cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about a deep learning solution for Chinese Word Segmentation (CWS) challenge, which is a natural language processing (NLP) task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces an innovative design for the model architecture, which involves the use of artificial tokens and shared layers, indicating a focus on machine learning (ML) techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on large-scale datasets, which could indicate a potential fit for cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
